HEADWORD: Synapticula
<hw>Syn`ap*tic"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Synapticulae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.,
dim. from Gr. <?/ fastened together.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One
of numerous calcareous processes which extend between, and unite, the
adjacent septa of certain corals, especially of the fungian
corals.</def>⟦br⟧
